name: San Fernando Valley Rescue Mission
review_text: A wonderful place! Accepts clothing and household items for scheduled pick up from your location. A worthy place to give donations.

name: San Fernando Valley Rescue Mission
review_text: I first learned about the shelter when I volunteered and helped serve brunch to the guest on a Saturday morning. I got a chance to work alongside the staff and cook a hot meal. I was also able to sit down with the families and have breakfast with them. They were very grateful for the love and support the staff and the program itself had offered them. Fast forward a couple of years later, I am blessed to now be working here as part of the team that creates a space filled with hope and the love of God for all who walk through our doors. I am grateful for the generosity of the community and donors who generously share their time and finances to keep this program running. I am grateful to be working under such wonderful, God-fearing leadership who genuinely cares for the holistic well-being of the families who enter our program.

name: San Fernando Valley Rescue Mission
review_text: This foundation is really helpful and has the most dedicated staff.  It is a  non profit organization whom run strictly off of donations, and willing to accommodate you if you are experiencing Homelessness. With open arms they welcome you into a 3 month program to help you get on your feet and consistent on assisting you with the right essentials,needs, and goals to help you maintain a routine into moving into your own place once the program is completed. Drug Free Drama Free and nothing but a positive environment even during this COVID 19 pandemic.

name: San Fernando Valley Rescue Mission
review_text: It was okay. Must be out from 7:30-4:00 everyday. Curfew is 6:00 every day when dinner is served. Food was ok. Not alot of fruit. Or veggies. Outdoor food you must bring enough for all families in the shelter. Nice building. 90 day stay. Random testing. Strict program. 30 day probation period. During that time u myst share an open dorm with multiple families. If you complain about anything like others children running up and slapping your kid they may say its not the place for you at your 30 day review. Clean bathrooms. Must be able to work. They have jobs they are partnered with to help you get a job quicker.
